  "answer": "- $S E_b=\\frac{s_{Y \\mid x}}{\\sqrt{n-1} \\cdot s_X}=\\frac{8.349}{\\sqrt{11-1} \\cdot 378.451}=0.006976$\n- For $95 \\%$ confidence, use $t_{n-2,1-(\\alpha / 2)}=t_{9,975}=2.262$\n- The $95 \\%$ confidence interval for $\\beta=b \\pm t_{n-1,1-9} \\cdot S E_b=0.02884 \\pm (2.262)(0.006976)=0.02884 \\pm 0.01578=(0.00706$ to 0.03862$)$.",
